        "content": "<p>As a challenge I am trying to complete the fix for the 'bad diamond' in C07S01 in MIL:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This story then continues with incorporating a <code>zsmul</code> field into the definition of groups and similar tricks.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I am using the following as a failing test case to work against</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inst</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Module₂</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inferInstance</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inst</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">smul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">selfModule₂</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">smul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It should pass if I fix the diamond and currently it fails at <code>rfl</code>.</p>\n<p>But the test case is still failing and I am feeling lost in the pile of type-classes. I get that the solution is to stick <code>nsmul</code> and <code>zsmul</code> as early in the semigroup and groups (even though not necessarily needed) so that I can overwrite them on the \\Z instances with the simple Z multiplication.</p>\n<p>Should I be introducing explicit instance of <code>selfModule \\Z</code> like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" 